The paper deals with improving the classification results of Gaussian SVM by considering local geometry-dependent feature space projection. This is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning, specifically in the area of support vector machines. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with datasets and their partitioning, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of k-means clustering also suggests a possible fit under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
